description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within Hertfordshire Community Trust for an enthusiastic and compassionate Specialist Palliative Care Nurse to join our team based in North Hertfordshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your expert skills, knowledge and experience will support patients and their families with progressive and life limiting illnesses who require complex symptom management, psychological and end of life care within the community. You will be part of a 7 day week team, working closely with community nursing teams, local hospitals, hospices and GPs ensuring a responsive and effective service for our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will demonstrate enthusiasm for the specialty as well as strong clinical leadership skills and a desire to develop the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an opportunity to work in a supportive and friendly team where professional development opportunities will be available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to the basic salary, this post attracts a High Cost Area Supplement of 5% of basic salary subject to a minimum payment of £1,034 and a maximum payment of £1,791 per annum.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must hold a full valid driving licence and have access to a car to use regularly for business purposes is essential (unless you have a disability as defined by the Equality Act 2010).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date 23rd November.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Jemma Finch&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Professional Clinical Lead Specialist Palliative and End of Life Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: jemma.finch1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07867 141829&lt;/p&gt;
